BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:rDZ43azQb4lmoCM4MIbS8
SUMMARY:College Possible Washington Coffee Chat
DTSTAMP:20260413T005344Z
DTSTART:20260423T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Coffee Chat with College Possible Washington Join College Possi
	ble Washington for a casual Coffee Chat with Executive Director Lauren Tre
	acy. This informal gathering is an opportunity for local partners\, suppor
	ters\, and community members to connect and learn more about our work supp
	orting students on their path to a college degree. College Possible Washin
	gton provides intensive college access and success programming for student
	s from low-income backgrounds and those who are the first in their familie
	s to attend college. Through personalized coaching and proven support from
	 high school through college graduation\, we help students overcome barrie
	rs and achieve their educational goals. We’ll share updates on our new ful
	l-time staff model\, our three-year strategic plan\, and the impact of our
	 programs across the greater Seattle area. Attendees will also have the ch
	ance to ask questions and engage in conversation about the organization’s 
	direction and community partnerships. Date: Thursday\, April 23rd Time: 11
	:00 AM – 1:00 PM \\(drop-in hours\\) Location: Renton Chamber of Commerce 
	To let us know you are coming\, please complete this form.  We look forwar
	d to connecting with you!\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details
	/college-possible-washington-coffee-chat/18407746/2026-04-23T00\n\nFrom SE
	Atoday - Food & Drink
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/college-possible-washingt
	on-coffee-chat/18407746/2026-04-23T00
LOCATION:SCERA\, 625 S. 4th Street\, Renton\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-food
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Food & Drink
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
